## Summary

Added **Hon Mun** (Nha Trang, Vietnam) — `nha-trang-vietnam-hon-mun`.

**Why this pick:** The coverage-gaps file was stale — its top Indo-Pacific entries (SS Yongala, Coron, Lembeh, Wakatobi, Anilao, etc.) are all already in `sites.json` (221 sites, very comprehensive). I diffed all in-region locations against actual sites and found only two with **zero** sites: Nha Trang (Vietnam) and Jeju (South Korea). Both countries are in-region. Hon Mun won on two counts: it's Vietnam's premier dive destination and first marine protected area ("Southeast Asia's Aquarium," ~1,500 species per WWF), **and** it had a usable, license-safe underwater hero on Commons — Jeju had essentially none.

**Hero image:** `Vietnam_Nha_Trang_Scuba_Diving_2009_-_4163161777.jpg` (CC BY 2.0, 3488×2616) — a wide reef scene of a school of reef fish over a table coral at Nha Trang, matching the description's reef-biodiversity focus rather than a generic stand-in. Verified it resolves (HTTP 206 on range request) and viewed it directly alongside 5 alternates.

**Facts verified across sources:** first MPA designated 2001, ~1,500 species, ~14 km SE of Nha Trang (coords 12.166, 109.302), dry-season (Feb–Sep) clarity vs. Oct–Dec northeast-monsoon murk, named sites (Madonna Rock swim-throughs, Hon Mun Wall). 12 month-varied condition entries, clean additive diff (225 insertions, 0 deletions), JSON validates.

